An anti-inflammatory response of an organic food intervention treatment by reducing pesticide exposures in children of Cyprus: a cluster-randomized crossover trial - Part 2

Regression analysis (mixed effects models)

This script includes the regression analysis (Part 2). The output of the Part 1 script needs to be created (produced_data/meas1).

Visualization

Visualize the association between the creatinine adjusted crp measurements and the time and the non creatinine crp adjusted measurements and the days from treatment.

  • Both measurements (creatinine adjusted crp and non creatinine adjusted crp) are log transformed.

Plot 1. Association between the CRP measurements (adjusted and non adjusted) and the days from treatment for the organic phase

Plot 2. Association between the CRP measurements (adjusted and non adjusted) and the days from treatment for the conventional phase

Plot 3. Association between the creatinine adjusted CRP measurements and the days from treatment for each phase

Plot 4. Association between the non-creatinine adjusted CRP measurements and the days from treatment for each phase

Main analysis

All models were adjusted for the baseline value of the outcome.

All models were adjusted for the creatinine levels using two ways:

  • CRP and pesticides measurements were divided with the respective creatinine measurements
  • Creatinine was included as a fixed effect

Initial model (model for objective 1):

  • Random part: participants
  • Fixed effect: treatment condition (organic or conventional) and time (days of treatment, where time=0 was the start of the treatment)
  • Interaction term: time*phase
  • Check interaction term:
  • if p-value>0.05 remove from the model

Log creatinine adjusted CRP ~ baseline log creatinine adjusted CRP + DaysfromTreatment + phase + (phase*DaysfromTreatment if p<0.05) + random()

Models for objective 2

A second model was made to assess the association between biomarker of exposure to pesticides (3-PBA and 6-CN, separately) and biomarker of inflammation (CRP).

  • Random part: participants
  • Fixed effect: each biomarker of exposure to pesticides, time (days of treatment, where time=0 was the start of the treatment), age and sex

Log creatinine adjusted CRP ~ Log creatinine adjusted baseline CRP + 6-CN (binary) + DaysfromTreatment + sex + baseline age + random()
